0) Goal and guiding constraints

Goal: Modern GNU social-style platform:

microblog + replies + boosts + likes

local groups/communities (GNU social flavor)

ActivityPub federation that works with Mastodon first

modern login options (email/passkeys + optional social/OIDC providers)

Key constraint: Federation is a hostile internet protocol. Build it like you’d build an exposed security service: strict parsing, idempotency, SSRF defenses, rate limiting, audit logs.

Why target Mastodon first: it’s the biggest ActivityPub microblog “reference implementation” in practice, and its docs tell you what actually needs to work in the wild.

1) Tech choices (default)

Backend: Go
DB: Postgres
Queue/Cache: Redis
Media: local disk now, S3 later
Frontend: optional later (API-first)

(You can swap Go for Node/TS or Elixir; the interfaces don’t change.)

