13) Quick test checklist (minimum viable “it federates”)

WebFinger resolves acct:alice@domain to actor URL

Mastodon can discover actor JSON

Mastodon follow triggers inbox Follow and you reply Accept

Posting locally delivers Create to remote follower inboxes

Undo/Delete behave sensibly (don’t resurrect objects; keep tombstones or soft-delete)

14) What not to do (common traps)

Don’t fetch arbitrary URLs without SSRF controls (federation will try to trick you).

Don’t rely on “spec says so” — rely on interop tests with Mastodon behavior.

Don’t make groups federated until the base is stable.

Don’t ship 4 social logins before you’ve shipped a working Fediverse loop.